      "content": "**Structural alerts vs classic hERG binders**\n- Typical high-risk hERG pharmacophore: **cationic basic center (piperidine/tertiary amine) + two hydrophobes/aromatics** at the right spacing.\n- This molecule **does have two hydrophobic/aromatic domains**, but the \u201cbasic center\u201d is **an amide N**, which is usually **non-protonated** at physiological pH.",
