      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "## 2) SAR reasoning (why these features push hERG risk up/down)\n**Factors increasing hERG likelihood**\n- **Two aromatic rings** (\u03c0\u2013\u03c0 interactions with hERG aromatic residues such as Tyr/Phe in the cavity are common in blockers).\n- **High lipophilicity** likely (two aryls + tert-butyl-like group + difluoro substituents), which often correlates with hERG binding.\n- **Rigid, preorganized 3D shape** can reduce entropic penalty and sometimes improves fit in the hERG cavity.",
