      "step_type": "reasoning",
      "content": "**Factors decreasing hERG likelihood (major)**\n- **Lack of a cationic/basic amine at pH 7.4**:\n  - The **amide nitrogen is strongly resonance-stabilized** and typically **not protonated** (very low basicity).\n  - Many potent hERG blockers rely on a **positively charged center** to engage electrostatic interactions deep in the channel cavity; removing that often drops potency substantially.\n- **Polar groups (amide carbonyl, alcohol, phenol)** increase H-bonding and may reduce effective membrane partitioning into the channel cavity relative to similarly lipophilic cationic amines (though this is not a guarantee).",
